description:
GetTransfer.com is an international transfer marketplace based in Cyprus. The platform provides transfer bookings and chauffeured car rentals at the best prices and currently operates in over 180 countries. Customers can order a transfer through a user-friendly mobile app which is available in over 20 languages. Since 2015 we have proved ourselves as a prospective and sustainable enterprise, which is reaffirmed by Travolution Awards, Globe Travel Awards, e.t.c. Still we keep developing the platform and improving our services, and now we are seeking for **Product manager.**

Responsibilities:

* Develop and execute product strategies and roadmaps;
* Conduct market research and competitive analysis to identify customer needs and trends;
* Collaborate with cross-functional teams to define product requirements and specifications;
* Work closely with engineering teams to ensure successful product development and delivery;
* Define and track key product metrics to measure success and drive improvements;
* Conduct user testing and gather feedback to inform product enhancements;
* Create wireframes, prototypes, and user stories to effectively communicate product features and functionality;
* Stay up-to-date with industry trends and emerging technologies.

Skills:

* Strong background in software development and familiarity with agile methodologies;
* Bachelor's degree in a technical discipline such as Computer Science or a related discipline or equivalent work experience required;
* 3+ years experience working in Information Technology or Digital Technology;
* Proficiency in analytics tools such as Excel or Google Analytics to gather insights and make data-driven decisions;
* Experience working with databases and conducting data analysis;
* Knowledge of wireframing tools to create visual representations of product features;
* Familiarity with project management software to track progress and collaborate with teams;
* Proficient in Microsoft Office suite (Word, Excel, PowerPoint);
* Ability to analyze complex problems and develop innovative solutions.

As a Product Manager, you will play a crucial role in driving the success of our products. You will have the opportunity to work on cutting-edge technologies while collaborating with talented cross-functional teams. If you are passionate about creating innovative products that solve real-world problems, we would love to hear from you. Apply now!

Job Type: Full-time

Salary: $3,000.00 - $5,000.00 per month

Benefits:

* Employee discount
* Relocation assistance

Compensation package:

* Monthly bonus

Experience level:

* 3 years

Schedule:

* Monday to Friday

Work Location: Remote
